5.body: Base Node is the base node. Each node is split up into three different sub classes. A Root Node is a node at the start of the tree. A Pure Node is a node without a end pin. A Single Node is a node which only allows one pin connection on the start pin and the end pin. A Multi Node is a node which allows multiple pin connections on the start pin and the end pin. There are script templates for each of these node types which can be found under the Create tab in the menu. A Graph Runner is the a script which can be added to any game object within the Scene to
5.title: Classes

6.title: AI Tool

7.body: To Install the AI Tool simply Download the Unity Package on the Github or grab the Git url and paste it into the package manager. This package does include some dependencies which is the new Unity Input System.
7.title: Installation

8.body: The AI Tool adds some new components which can be added to any object in the scene. If you selected a GameObject and click Add Component button there will be a new menu called AI node Tool. This menu will include all the current components currently avaible.
